edu.biu.scapi.midLayer.symmetricCrypto.encryption

Interface SymMultiplicativeHomomorphicEnc

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Eav, EncSecLevel, Indistinguishable, SecurityLevel, SymmetricEnc

    public interface SymMultiplicativeHomomorphicEnc
extends SymmetricEnc
    General interface for symmetric multiplicative homomorphic encryption. Such encryption scheme can compute the encryption of m1*m2, given only the encryptions of m1 and m2.
    Author:
    Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Yael Ejgenberg)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      SymmetricCiphertext multiply(SymmetricCiphertext c1, SymmetricCiphertext c2)
      Given two ciphers c1 = enc(p1), c2 = enc(p2) this function returns c1 * c2 = enc(p1 * p2)
